results.name: a(1) = 2; a(n+1) is the smallest prime not already in the sequence which differs from a(n) at every digit.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: 13 follows 29 as the smallest prime number not included earlier and differing at every digit position with 29.
program: f p ps = g ps where
| and $ zipWith (/=) p q = (read q :: Int) : f q (delete q ps)
